# LookingGlass Cyber CTC Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on

This software is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.

## Welcome to LookingGlass Cyber CTC Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on

#### The LookingGlass Cyber CTC Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on has been designed to collect incidents data from the CTC for use with Splunk.

#### Installation for a single server Splunk instance
Installing with Splunk Web for a single server Splunk instance
1) From the Splunk Web home screen, click the gear icon next to Apps.
2) Click Install app from file.
3) Locate Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_dhs_ctc.tar.gz and click Upload
4) If Splunk Enterprise prompts you, click Yes to restart

Installing via CLI for a single server Splunk instance
1) Upload the Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_dhs_ctc.tar.gz file to the Splunk instance
2) Extract the .tar.gz file in the apps directory of Splunk.  For example if your Splunk apps directory is located at /opt/splunk/etc/apps perform the following:
    a) sudo tar zxvf Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_dhs_ctc.tar.gz -C /opt/splunk/etc/apps
3) Restart Splunk using /opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart

#### Installation for a distributed server Splunk environment
NOTE: The LookingGlass Cyber CTC Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on needs to be installed on a heavy forwarder in a distributed environment

Installing with Splunk Web for a distributed server Splunk environment
1) From the Splunk Web home screen on a heavy forwarder, click the gear icon next to Apps.
2) Click Install app from file.
3) Locate Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_dhs_ctc.tar.gz and click Upload
4) If Splunk Enterprise prompts you, click Yes to restart

Installing via CLI for a distributed server Splunk environment
1) Upload the Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_dhs_ctc.tar.gz file to a heavy forwarder
2) Extract the .tar.gz file in the apps directory of Splunk.  For example if your Splunk apps directory is located at /opt/splunk/etc/apps perform the following:
    a) sudo tar zxvf Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_dhs_ctc.tar.gz -C /opt/splunk/etc/apps
3) Restart Splunk using /opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart

#### Configuration
Once the Splunk app has been installed, perform the following to configure the Technology Add-on:
1) From the Splunk Web home screen, click the gear icon next to Apps
2) From the list of Splunk apps and add-ons click on Set up under Actions for the LookingGlass Cyber CTC Data Feed app
3) Ensure that Enable CTC Integration is checked
4) Enter in the CTC Client ID in the CTC Client ID textbox.
NOTE: If you do not have either a Client ID or API Token, please contact support@lookingglasscyber.com to obtain them.
5) Ensure that the CTC API Username is ctc_api
6) Enter in the CTC API key that you will be using to pull data from in the CTC API Key text box.
7) (Optional) If the Splunk instance needs to use a proxy server to access the Internet ensure that Use a proxy server is checked
8) (Optional) Enter in the domain name and port information for the proxy server if the Splunk instance needs to use a proxy server to access the Internet
9) Click on Save in the lower right hand corner of the configuration screen when you are finished

NOTE: Since the API key is encrypted it will not be displayed in the UI after you save it and re-enter the setup screen

